Direct Known Subclasses:
OsmRawPbfGraphLoader
public abstract class RawPbfGraphLoader extends PbfGraphLoader
Base class for loading raw graphs from PBF files. In the OSM data specification, a raw graph contains data that has not been way-sectioned, where each edge is an OSM way. In the UniDb specification, the data is already way-sectioned and there is no such distinction.

    • validation

      public com.telenav.kivakit.validation.ValidationType validation()
      Returns:
      The kind of validation that should be performed on the data loaded by this graph loader. Many graph loaders validate all data with ValidationType.VALIDATE_ALL but some don't load complete data. An example of an incomplete graph loader is RawPbfGraphLoader, which does not load vertexes or relations. Another is WaySectioningGraphLoader, is incomplete because it does not load relations. These graph loaders may specify another kind of validation.

    • shouldStoreNodeLocation

      protected abstract boolean shouldStoreNodeLocation(PbfNode node)
      Determines if the given node's location should be stored. If this method returns true, the node's location must be stored in a memory-hungry map for later use. There are three different ways it can be determined if a node's location needs to be stored, depending on the subclass and its DataSpecification and the presence or absence of way node locations in the data: 
           1. If the PBF file has way node locations (as determined by the metadata section of the PBF file)
        then the method should return false as way node locations don't need to be stored
     2. If the PBF file contains OSM data, then the PbfDataAnalysis performed during the first pass
        has already determined which nodes are way nodes.
     3. In the case of UniDb data, there are no nodes in the file that are not way nodes and so each node
        must have its location stored (unless #1 is true), so the method should return true.
      Parameters:
      node - The node to inspect
      Returns:
      True if the node is a way node, and we should store its location in a map for later
